🧭 GOAL (Console-First POC)

You will:

✅ Create infra manually
✅ Deploy 1 real service on Amazon EKS
✅ Connect to ON-PREM (or simulate)
✅ Use:
	•	Amazon RDS for PostgreSQL
	•	Amazon MQ
	•	Argo CD (optional later)

👉 Then you convert everything → Terraform

⸻

🪜 STEP-BY-STEP (AWS CONSOLE LAB)

⸻

🧱 STEP 1: Create VPC (Console)

Go to:
👉 VPC → “Create VPC”

Settings:
	•	Name: fintech-vpc
	•	CIDR: 10.0.0.0/16
	•	AZs: 2
	•	Public + Private subnets
	•	NAT Gateway: 1 (cost optimized)

⸻

☸️ STEP 2: Create EKS Cluster

Go to:
👉 EKS → Create cluster

Config:
	•	Name: fintech-eks
	•	Kubernetes version: latest stable
	•	VPC: select above
	•	Endpoint: Public + Private

⸻

Add Node Group
	•	Instance: t3.medium (start cheap)
	•	Nodes: min=2, max=4

⸻

Connect

aws eks update-kubeconfig --region eu-central-1 --name fintech-eks
kubectl get nodes


⸻

🐘 STEP 3: Create PostgreSQL (RDS)

Go to:
👉 RDS → Create DB

Config:
	•	Engine: PostgreSQL
	•	Template: Production
	•	Instance: db.t3.micro (lab)
	•	Multi-AZ: OFF (for now)
	•	Public access: NO

⸻

👉 Note:
	•	Save endpoint
	•	Allow access from EKS security group

⸻

🐇 STEP 4: Create RabbitMQ

Go to:
👉 Amazon MQ → Create broker

Config:
	•	Engine: RabbitMQ
	•	Instance: mq.t3.micro
	•	Deployment: Single instance (lab)

⸻

👉 Save:
	•	Endpoint
	•	Username/password

⸻

🔐 STEP 5: Security Group Fix (IMPORTANT)

Allow:

EKS → RDS
	•	Port: 5432

EKS → MQ
	•	Port: 5671 / 5672

⸻

🚀 STEP 6: Deploy Test Service (Manual)

⸻

Create simple deployment

apiVersion: apps/v1
kind: Deployment
metadata:
  name: test-service
spec:
  replicas: 2
  selector:
    matchLabels:
      app: test
  template:
    metadata:
      labels:
        app: test
    spec:
      containers:
        - name: app
          image: nginx
          ports:
            - containerPort: 80


⸻


kubectl apply -f deployment.yaml
kubectl get pods


⸻

🌐 STEP 7: Expose via LoadBalancer

apiVersion: v1
kind: Service
metadata:
  name: test-service
spec:
  type: LoadBalancer
  selector:
    app: test
  ports:
    - port: 80
      targetPort: 80


⸻

👉 You now have:
	•	Public endpoint

⸻

🔌 STEP 8: Connect Service → RDS + MQ

Modify deployment:

env:
  - name: DB_HOST
    value: <rds-endpoint>
  - name: MQ_HOST
    value: <mq-endpoint>


⸻

